  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrase groups matter most for a Portugal itinerary?",
        "zh-CN": "去葡萄牙旅行时，最值得先准备哪几组短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Start with transport, dining, and hotel. That covers tram or train questions, cafe orders, apartment arrivals, and most first-day logistics in Portugal.",
        "zh-CN": "建议先看交通、餐饮和酒店三组，基本就能覆盖电车或火车询问、咖啡馆点单、公寓入住，以及葡萄牙第一天的大多数安排。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Why are payment and cafe phrases especially useful in Portugal?",
        "zh-CN": "为什么在葡萄牙旅行时，支付和咖啡馆短语特别实用？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Because you use them many times a day: at cafe counters, bakeries, smaller shops, and ticket desks. A short phrase saves time every time you stop for something small.",
        "zh-CN": "因为这些场景一天里会反复出现很多次，比如咖啡馆柜台、面包店、小店和售票处。每次停下来处理一点小事时，一句简短葡语都会帮你节省不少时间。"
      }
    }
  ]
